The paper discusses the security of a cryptographic scheme, which falls under the category of cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The paper also involves the analysis of the efficiency and randomness of the composition maps used in the scheme, which could be categorized under cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.SY (Systems and Control). Additionally, the paper involves the use of mathematical models and algorithms, which could be categorized under cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.NA (Numerical Analysis).
